name: LilacFox
review: The wider ones are great at getting the tiny brow hairs, personally I do not like the skinny ones. Too hard to use for me but I love how tiny they are and that they come with a case to keep them In.

name: rexie
review: Finally!! I've found a pair of tweezers that are not only perfect for my tiny toiletry bag but I've found a set that comes with 2 pairs and a cover. Yes!! The tips are sharp and have never let me down when it comes to plucking those stubborn stray eye brown hairs. They've even come in handy when my husband asked me to pluck out a tiny, stubborn, little ingrown hair that he'd had on his leg. My hands are fairly small, so these lil guys aren't too tiny for me. But, they may be too small for other folks. I think these are also perfect to keep in your first aid kit, especially the type that you'd send your kids to school with at the beginning of the year, or even for inside the trunk of your car. My Mom has borrowed them a few times to fix some of her clasps, on various jewelry pieces. They really come in handy.

review: I keep this product in my makeup bag and use for all kinds of tasks. I can do a quick brow cleanup or get rid of a stray anywhere.I love there cute design and handy size.

name: Tricia
review: I've been getting my eyebrows threaded every 2 weeks for the last two years, and since I lost my job, I had to stop going to the salon to get my eyebrows done. I bought these for the price and the great reviews I read, AND IT WORKS WONDERFULLY! I love that the tweezers are small & comes with a little pouch, so I can take it everywhere! Even if I did have enough money to get my eyebrows done again, I don't think I would because I've grown to love plucking my own eyebrows with these. Super easy to use & doesn't frustrate me like other tweezers that become too dull. These gets every single hair, from fine, to even the annoying little stubbles.
